						               													<description>A bluffing game where the aim is collect the most maki and sushi possible by bluffing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Contents: 18 Fish cards numbered 0-3&amp;#10;Rule cards for 10 languages.&amp;#10;21 Maki tokens.&amp;#10;11 Sushi tokens.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The deck of cards are shuffled and the first player draws the top three cards and secretly&amp;#10;announces a score lower than or equal to 9.&amp;#10;There are then the 2 possibilities.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A.The following player believes the announced score and takes the cards, whilst the first player wins a maki tile.The following player then draws the top card from the draw deck and announces a score still lower or equal to 9.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;B.The following player does not believe the score announced.&amp;#10;If the first players announced score was right he shows the cards, puts them beneath the draw deck and takes a maki tile. The following player then misses a turn.&amp;#10;The next player then draws 3 cards from the deck and play starts again.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a player announces 9 without bluffing he wins 2 Maki tiles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a player has 5 maki tiles, he exchanges them for 1 sushi Tile.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Depending on the players and time available the winner of the game is the first to obtain 1 or 2 Sushi tiles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Inspired by Perudo&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
